2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new type of clustering criteria for feature engineering in NLP, which involves machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing more effective methods for NLP tasks, which is a key area of research in AI. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with feature engineering for NLP tasks, which is also relevant to information retrieval tasks. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve discussions on the computational complexity of the proposed method.
